Titanic - Machine Learning from Disaster

Problem Definition¶

In a statement,

Knowing from a training set of samples listing passengers who survived or did not survive the Titanic disaster, can our model determine based on a given test dataset not containing the survival information, if these passengers in the test dataset survived or not.

Function to create count and distribution visualisations¶

In [28]:
def plot_count_dist(data, label_column, target_column, figsize=(20, 5)):
    """
    Function to plot counts and distributions of a label variable and 
    target variable side by side.
    ::param_data:: = target dataframe
    ::param_label_column:: = binary labelled column
    ::param_target_column:: = column you want to view counts and distributions
    ::param_figsize:: = size of figure (width, height)
    """
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=figsize)
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    sns.countplot(y=target_column, data=data);
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    sns.distplot(data.loc[data[label_column] == 1][target_column], 
                 kde_kws={"label": "Survived"});
    sns.distplot(data.loc[data[label_column] == 0][target_column], 
                 kde_kws={"label": "Did not survive"});

2. Feature Encoding¶

Now we have our two sub dataframes ready. We can encode the features so they're ready to be used with our machine learning models.

In [53]:
# One hot encode the categorical columns
df_embarked_one_hot = pd.get_dummies(df['Embarked'], 
                                     prefix='embarked')

df_sex_one_hot = pd.get_dummies(df['Sex'], 
                                prefix='sex')

df_plcass_one_hot = pd.get_dummies(df['Pclass'], 
                                   prefix='pclass')
In [54]:
# Combine the one hot encoded columns with df_con_enc
df_enc = pd.concat([df, 
                        df_embarked_one_hot, 
                        df_sex_one_hot, 
                        df_plcass_one_hot], axis=1)

# Drop the original categorical columns (because now they've been one hot encoded)
df_enc = df_enc.drop(['Pclass', 'Sex', 'Embarked'], axis=1)

print("Classification Report: \n", classification_report(y_test, pred))
